snippet.textDisplay: I love this so much. To me, this is what makes Nintendo so special and stand out compared to other gaming companies. Nintendo may not have the most powerful consoles or most up-to-date technology. But there’s a certain quality and polish to their games that honestly can’t be competed with. Ever since I can remember Nintendo has this way of bringing out the happiest memories and sentimental attachment that I just can’t get anywhere else. I can go on playing AC, Zelda, etc. for HOURS and never get burnt out or bored. Then when I finish those games I get this intense bittersweet feeling and can’t help but replay/revisit it after a few months. Nintendo has something for everyone regardless of your age. I don’t think I’ll ever really outgrow their games; they’re truly timeless, and she’s living proof of that!
snippet.textOriginal: I love this so much. To me, this is what makes Nintendo so special and stand out compared to other gaming companies. For the Filbert amiibo: once she’s unlocked the campsite and she’s invited her first campsite visitor (you’re required to invite your first visitor no matter what) you will have the option after talking to Tom Nook to invite villagers through amiibo! For 3 days, use your nook atm and invite Filbert and craft him his desired DIY (he’ll give you the recipe for it) and then you can invite him to live with you on the island! Just giving you some help since I just went through it with my Stitches amiibo!

I really hope you and your grandmother and family are doing alright! It’s crazy right now but this is the perfect time to cozy up inside and play animal crossing for hours and hours! Stay safe and healthy! 🥰
